<subSubSection pageId="29" pageNumber="422" type="reference_group">
<paragraph blockId="29.[2052,2646,1010,1436]" box="[2053,2643,1010,1043]" pageId="29" pageNumber="422">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[2053,2208,1010,1043]" pageId="29" pageNumber="422">Taxonomy.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authority="Cope, 1862" authorityName="Cope" authorityYear="1862" box="[2223,2638,1010,1043]" class="Mammalia" family="Soricidae" genus="Neosorex" kingdom="Animalia" order="Soricomorpha" pageId="29" pageNumber="422" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="albibarbis">Neosorex albibarbis Cope, 1862</taxonomicName>
,
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="29.[2052,2646,1010,1436]" pageId="29" pageNumber="422">
<materialsCitation pageId="29" pageNumber="422">“Profile Lake, in the Franconia Mountains [Grafton Co.], New Hampshire,”</materialsCitation>
USA. 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Cope" baseAuthorityYear="1862" box="[2054,2253,1133,1162]" class="Mammalia" family="Soricidae" genus="Sorex" kingdom="Animalia" order="Soricomorpha" pageId="29" pageNumber="422" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="albibarbis">Sorex albibarbis</taxonomicName>
is in the 
<taxonomicName authorityName="J. Richardson" authorityYear="1828" box="[2401,2547,1133,1162]" class="Mammalia" family="Soricidae" genus="Sorex" kingdom="Animalia" order="Soricomorpha" pageId="29" pageNumber="422" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="palustris">S. palustris</taxonomicName>
group and subgenus Ofisorex; it is sister to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="J. Richardson" authorityYear="1828" class="Mammalia" family="Soricidae" genus="Sorex" kingdom="Animalia" order="Soricomorpha" pageId="29" pageNumber="422" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="palustris">S. palustris</taxonomicName>
, of which it was previously included as a subspecies of. Although not all subspecies have been sampled, S. albibarbis is genetically distinguishable from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="J. Richardson" authorityYear="1828" box="[2498,2646,1325,1358]" class="Mammalia" family="Soricidae" genus="Sorex" kingdom="Animalia" order="Soricomorpha" pageId="29" pageNumber="422" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="palustris">S. palustris</taxonomicName>
along with S. navigator. Additional studies are needed to distinguish S. albibarbis from
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="29.[1435,2645,1442,3090]" pageId="29" pageNumber="422">
the other two water shrews morphologically. Distributional limits between S. albibarbis and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="J. Richardson" authorityYear="1828" box="[1503,1643,1482,1515]" class="Mammalia" family="Soricidae" genus="Sorex" kingdom="Animalia" order="Soricomorpha" pageId="29" pageNumber="422" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="palustris">S. palustris</taxonomicName>
are still very uncertain. Because ofthis confusion,all ecological data for S. albibarbis, S. navigator, and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="J. Richardson" authorityYear="1828" box="[1853,1996,1521,1554]" class="Mammalia" family="Soricidae" genus="Sorex" kingdom="Animalia" order="Soricomorpha" pageId="29" pageNumber="422" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="palustris">S. palustris</taxonomicName>
are listed under 
<taxonomicName authorityName="J. Richardson" authorityYear="1828" box="[2241,2384,1521,1554]" class="Mammalia" family="Soricidae" genus="Sorex" kingdom="Animalia" order="Soricomorpha" pageId="29" pageNumber="422" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="palustris">S. palustris</taxonomicName>
here. Five subspecies recognized.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
